------------- Environment Variables --------------

GOROOT: points to your binary installation of Go
GOPATH: points to your go workspace
GOBIN: points to the binary of package installations

------------- Commands --------------

go help: prints go commands helper
go version: prints the go version
go env: prints the go environment variables
go fmt: formatter (its like prettier)
go fmt ./...: format everything in the repo

go run: run the go file
go build: compiles the code into a .exe
go install: install the go file into the GOBIN

go mod init example.com/username/repo: initialize module
go list -m all: show all dependencies
go list -m -versions package: show all existent versions of package
go get package: install dependency
go get package@0.0.x: install dependency at version 0.0.x

------------------ CheatSheet --------------------------
- Initial code
  package main

  import (
    "fmt"
  )

  func main() {
    fmt.Println("Hello, playground")
  }

- Var Declaration
  Can be used at the Package Level
  Can be used without assign a initial value (assign Zero Value)

  var x = 10
  var y string = "Text"
  var z bool

- Short Declaration
  x := 10
  y := "Text

- Types
  int, bool, string,
  var y string = "Text"

  type MyType int

  var z MyType = int